                <h4>Background</h4>
                <h3>1: INTRODUCTION AND PROJECT OVERVIEW</h3>
                <h5>1.1 Introduction.</h5>
                <p>
                    Thanks to the initiatives and all individuals that support the girl child in our communities due to
                    the many female challenges all over the world. That is one of the greatest achievements humanity has
                    come to.
                </p>
                <p>
                    That as a result has brought the need to start an initiative that also caters for the boy child.
                </p>
                <p>
                    This is an initiative started with an intention of rebuilding, reinstating, encouraging,
                    rehabilitating and reminding the boy child of his place in society.
                </p>
                <p>
                    This project comes consequently to remind everyone about the boy child. He has been forgotten and
                    this makes the demolition of the female problems almost impossible. This comes because of many
                    reasons one of them being that the girl child is not alone in this world, and will consequently
                    marry the boy child and have to spend all their lives together.
                </p>
                <p>
                    This has been noticed as the research conducted by the Uganda National Bureau of Statistics shows
                    that the number of boys that has dropped out of school in Uganda because they don’t want has risen
                    to 4 per 10 male dropouts, in the rural areas the number of boys facing child abuse has risen up to
                    84%.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The number of school dropouts is currently on the increase for the boys as the issue is being
                    tackled for the girl child, increased drug usage among the boy child, the boy child is being tackled
                    out of the different highly earning fields in the work force i.e. the females in the manufacturing
                    sector, trade sector is more than that of the male who are engaged in small earning sectors like
                    construction, transportation, and agriculture and these are very low earning sectors, more boys are
                    engaged in law breaking i.e. theft, e.tc.
                </p>
                <p>They account for 94.5% of the people in jail yet they are
                    bread winners and also more males drop out of school i.e. among people of 16-24 years 7%of the males
                    are high school dropouts and 5% of the females are high school drop outs according to UBOS as for
                    2019.
                </p>
                <p>
                    In addition, also the boy child being ignored also renders some of the would be achievements of the
                    women emancipation program useless this is a consequence as the two will get married and the boy is
                    ignorant on the new ways the marriages are handled since they differ from the ancient ones.
                </p>
                <p>
                    These new marriages include sharing house cores which many boys aren’t aware about and yet the girls
                    are being educated about the new systems in marriages therefore making the family instabilities very
                    rampant
                </p>

                <h5>1.2 Project description</h5>
                <p>
                    Boys are not prepared for their new roles in societies as fathers’ role models uncles leaders e.tc
                    and yet they need this guidance in order to make good examples and role models to the society. This
                    has forced many boys to take on habits such as drug usage, theft, e.tc.
                </p>
                <p>
                    This project will target the group of boys that are between the ages of 12-30 years of age. These
                    such boys are ignored in many ways such as, when offering education sponsorships, when providing
                    guidance especially in families as more emphasis is put on the girl child, and in many other areas.
                    The boy child is not given priority in any sector as they are not prioritized when giving out
                    scholarships, jobs, offering counselling and guidance, therefore the boys do not know their role in
                    society and yet a lot is expected out of them. They are not directed and prioritized and this broods
                    the different behavior such as drug usage etc. that bring room to social disorders such as theft,
                    kidnapping rape etc.
                </p>
                <p>
                    These challenges came to notice as of the figures published by the UBOS showing the rates of
                    employment in terms of gender showing that as more women are employed, more men are being
                    unemployed, the levels of child abuse in the villages are now high among the boys, the dropout rate
                    is now growing for boys, the drug consumption rate is rampant among boys, the gender committing more
                    of the social evils are men, and it has been noted that in families also men face more spousal abuse
                    right now(according to figures in 2014) by UNBOS.
                </p>
                <p>
                    This project will use different approaches such as through offering sponsorships majorly to the boy
                    child to encourage them attain education, offer free therapy, rehabilitation and follow up to the
                    drug intoxicated youths, offer free job training, male empowerment conferences to restore the pride
                    of the male children and youths. These will help reduces on the social evils committed in the
                    society such as theft drug abuse rape defilement.
                </p>

