                <h3>3: PROJECT DETAILS</h3>
                <h5>3.1 Project goals and details</h5>
                <p>
                    This project is new with objectives not set to meet the needs of the boy child in particular. This
                    is an initiative that looks at the challenges faced by the boy child in Uganda both in rural and
                    urban centers
                </p>

                <h5>3.2 Specific objectives</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>To eradicate drug usage among the youths in the country especially in urban centers.</li>
                    <li>To offer education to the financially handicapped males and females with having males as
                        superior at all levels of education</li>
                    <li>To offer free rehabilitation and therapy to those using drugs and those males who have faced
                        psychological torture.</li>
                    <li>To offer new job traning in order to reduce the unemployment among the boys in society.</li>
                    <li>To restore the boy child pride amongst the boy and this will help encourage boys to take up
                        their manly responsibilities.</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>3.3 Methods/strategies of promoting the Project objectives</h5>
                <p>
                    This project has put in place many different ways to solve the problems and achieve the objectives
                    it has in place.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        There shall be conferences that are organized twice a year in order to educate the boy child on
                        their roles and how they overcome the social pressure. This will also include the sensitization
                        of the general public on how to grow their boy children into the responsible men they want them
                        to be.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The project will also have in place full sponsorships to the boy child majorly although this
                        will also cater for the girl child. This will be put in place in order to ensure that they get
                        educated to the tertiary institutions. This will solve the problem of dropping out.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        There will be job training sessions that will train the boy child on the different jobs. This
                        will majorly constitute of technical jobs which are taught in technical institutions will be
                        provided at no fee charged.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The project will also be running adverts whose main use shall be to encourage and advocate for
                        boy child support. These shall be run on televisions radios newspapers social media platform to
                        enhance knowledge on how and the need of boy child support. These are some of the ways the
                        project shall bring awareness to the public about the boy child.
                    </li>
                </ul>

