                <h5>Outcomes and impacts of the project</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        There shall be increased employment amongst the boys in the society due to the new job training
                        sessions that shall be conducted and this will consequently put a reduction on the social evils
                        such as theft which are a result of unemployment. This impact on society will make it harmonious
                        and a happy place for the people in society.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The project will also provide the rehabilitation programs to those emotionally hurt people and
                        drug users and this is an individual achievement as it will improve their lives after the
                        therapy. This will reduce drug usage and other vices that accompany the use of drugs amongst the
                        youths.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The conferences intended to be hosted intend to build a positive belief among the boys. It also
                        intends to teach them their responsibilities in this changing modern society. This will majorly
                        change the picture that boys have to their female counterparts as this will also boost their
                        respect for the girl child this consequently solves many issues e.g. sharing responsibilities,
                        domestic violence etc.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        This project looks forward to improving the education of the boy child and that of the girl
                        child. Though this project is entitled to helping the boy child the girl child in need of
                        support of education shall be also helped. This in turn shall increase the number of educated
                        youths which gives them an advantage to access relevant services that were looked as irrelevant
                    </li>
                </ul>

